  "texts": [
    "This suggests that ChatGPT helped students present their ideas more clearly and logically.",
    "In precision, the experimental group also outperformed the control group (3.4 vs. 2.6), indicating that using ChatGPT allowed students to generate more accurate content with fewer errors.Regarding originality, the experimental group showed better performance (3.4) compared to the control group (2.8), which may be due to ChatGPT ability to inspire novel ideas and creative approaches in students' work.",
    "In the dimension of content depth, both groups obtained similar scores, although the experimental group was slightly superior (3.2 vs. 3.0), suggesting that ChatGPT can also contribute to a deeper exploration of research topics.Problem-solving ability showed similar averages between both groups, with the experimental group again slightly superior (3.2 vs. 3.0), indicating that ChatGPT can assist in identifying and solving complex problems.",
    "However, in the use of sources, the control group outperformed the experimental group (3.4 vs. 2.2).",
    "This suggests that while ChatGPT is useful in many aspects, traditional methods are still more effective for properly managing and referencing bibliographic sources, a crucial aspect in academic research.In summary, the experimental group tends to achieve better averages in most evaluative criteria, except in the use of sources, where the control group shows superior performance."
